{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01GMM9FNZGXHWEirR3BMoUoo","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Perfect! Now I have a complete picture. Let me create a comprehensive summary of my findings:\n\n## Summary of Findings\n\nI've thoroughly explored the cloche codebase and identified the workflow view UI code and the issue with file contents loading. Here are the key files and the problem:\n\n### **Key Files Found:**\n\n1. **Frontend UI Template (Workflow View)**\n   - `/workspace/internal/adapters/web/templates/project_detail.html` (lines 40-284)\n   - Contains the \"Workflows\" panel with step display and drawer for step details\n   - Lines 251-284: `openDrawer()` function that shows step information\n\n2. **Backend Handler Code (Step Content API)**\n   - `/workspace/internal/adapters/web/handler.go` (lines 1134-1199)\n   - Function: `handleAPIStepContent()` - serves the API endpoint for loading step file contents\n   - Route registered at line 156: `GET /api/projects/{name}/workflows/{workflow}/steps/{step}/content`\n\n3. **Static Assets (Styling)**\n   - `/workspace/internal/adapters/web/static/style.css` (entire file)\n   - Styling for drawer, step display, and UI components\n\n4. **Layout Template**\n   - `/workspace/internal/adapters/web/templates/layout.html` (basic HTML structure)\n\n5. **Run Detail Template**\n   - `/workspace/internal/adapters/web/templates/run_detail.html` (contains step execution view)\n\n### **The Problem: Filename Display Without Content Loading**\n\nThe issue is in the **workflow step drawer** (`project_detail.html`, lines 251-284):\n\n**Step 1: Display Phase (Lines 257-272)**\n- The drawer shows the step's filename/path from `step.config` (line 264)\n- Displays filename for `prompt`, `command`, or `script` config keys\n- Shows \"Loading content...\" message (line 269)\n\n**Step 2: Fetch Phase (Lines 274-283)**\n- Fetches file contents via: `/api/projects/{projectLabel}/workflows/{workflowName}/steps/{stepName}/content`\n- The fetch handler in `handler.go` (lines 1177-1183) tries to read the file but may fail:\n  - `os.ReadFile(filepath.Join(dir, prompt))` \n  - If the file doesn't exist or can't be read, it falls through\n  - Only displays \"No content available\" if all checks fail\n\n**The Bug Flow:**\n1. User clicks on a step node in the workflow DAG (line 233)\n2. `openDrawer()` is called with workflow and step name\n3. Drawer displays the filename from step config (line 264) ✓ Works\n4. Frontend fetches content via API (line 274)\n5. Backend `handleAPIStepContent()` tries to read the file at path (line 1178)\n6. If file not found or error occurs, it falls through to other config types without properly signaling success/failure\n7. If all configs fail to load, returns 404 \"no content available\" (line 1198)\n8. But the drawer already shows the filename, so user sees filename but no content\n\n### **Root Causes:**\n\n1. **File Path Resolution**: The handler joins the file path with `dir` (line 1178): `filepath.Join(dir, prompt)`, but `prompt` in the config might be a relative path that doesn't resolve correctly from the project directory.\n\n2. **Silent Failures**: If `os.ReadFile()` fails (lines 1179, 1189), the code continues without logging or indicating why it failed.\n\n3. **Incomplete Error Handling**: The function returns \"no content available\" (line 1198) without distinguishing between \"file doesn't exist,\" \"permission denied,\" \"file is empty,\" etc.\n\n4. **No Fallback Display**: The frontend shows \"No content available\" but doesn't help the user understand why (missing file? wrong path? unreadable?).\n\n### **API Route and Template Summary:**\n\n- **API Endpoint**: `GET /api/projects/{name}/workflows/{workflow}/steps/{step}/content`\n- **Frontend Fetch**: Line 274 in `project_detail.html`\n- **Handler**: `handleAPIStepContent()` at `/workspace/internal/adapters/web/handler.go:1134`\n- **Drawer Component**: Lines 40-47 of `project_detail.html` (HTML structure)\n- **Drawer JavaScript Logic**: Lines 251-284 of `project_detail.html` (openDrawer function)\n\nAll relevant code is in `/workspace/internal/adapters/web/` directory, with templates in `templates/` and Go handlers in `handler.go`."},{"type":"text","text":"agentId: aac18c6eeab385e48 (for resuming to continue this agent's work if needed)\n<usage>total_tokens: 54233\ntool_uses: 16\nduration_ms: 32613</usage>"}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"052fc540-1ffc-410e-aea3-964a1bf4fcbd","uuid":"8c5890a8-4aa5-43f0-a86b-9260dd45810e","tool_use_result":{"status":"completed","prompt":"I need to find the workflow view UI code where clicking on steps shows filename but doesn't load file contents. This is a Go project called \"cloche\" with a web UI. Search for:\n\n1. Any web/frontend files (HTML, JS, CSS, templates) related to workflow view or step display\n2. Any Go handler code that serves workflow/step data\n3. Any API endpoints related to loading step file contents\n4. Search for keywords like \"workflow\", \"step\", \"prompt\", \"contents\", \"filename\", \"loadFile\", \"fileContent\" across the codebase\n\nBe very thorough - check cmd/, internal/, web/, static/, templates/, ui/, frontend/ directories and any embedded files.","agentId":"aac18c6eeab385e48","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Perfect! Now I have a complete picture. Let me create a comprehensive summary of my findings:\n\n## Summary of Findings\n\nI've thoroughly explored the cloche codebase and identified the workflow view UI code and the issue with file contents loading. Here are the key files and the problem:\n\n### **Key Files Found:**\n\n1. **Frontend UI Template (Workflow View)**\n   - `/workspace/internal/adapters/web/templates/project_detail.html` (lines 40-284)\n   - Contains the \"Workflows\" panel with step display and drawer for step details\n   - Lines 251-284: `openDrawer()` function that shows step information\n\n2. **Backend Handler Code (Step Content API)**\n   - `/workspace/internal/adapters/web/handler.go` (lines 1134-1199)\n   - Function: `handleAPIStepContent()` - serves the API endpoint for loading step file contents\n   - Route registered at line 156: `GET /api/projects/{name}/workflows/{workflow}/steps/{step}/content`\n\n3. **Static Assets (Styling)**\n   - `/workspace/internal/adapters/web/static/style.css` (entire file)\n   - Styling for drawer, step display, and UI components\n\n4. **Layout Template**\n   - `/workspace/internal/adapters/web/templates/layout.html` (basic HTML structure)\n\n5. **Run Detail Template**\n   - `/workspace/internal/adapters/web/templates/run_detail.html` (contains step execution view)\n\n### **The Problem: Filename Display Without Content Loading**\n\nThe issue is in the **workflow step drawer** (`project_detail.html`, lines 251-284):\n\n**Step 1: Display Phase (Lines 257-272)**\n- The drawer shows the step's filename/path from `step.config` (line 264)\n- Displays filename for `prompt`, `command`, or `script` config keys\n- Shows \"Loading content...\" message (line 269)\n\n**Step 2: Fetch Phase (Lines 274-283)**\n- Fetches file contents via: `/api/projects/{projectLabel}/workflows/{workflowName}/steps/{stepName}/content`\n- The fetch handler in `handler.go` (lines 1177-1183) tries to read the file but may fail:\n  - `os.ReadFile(filepath.Join(dir, prompt))` \n  - If the file doesn't exist or can't be read, it falls through\n  - Only displays \"No content available\" if all checks fail\n\n**The Bug Flow:**\n1. User clicks on a step node in the workflow DAG (line 233)\n2. `openDrawer()` is called with workflow and step name\n3. Drawer displays the filename from step config (line 264) ✓ Works\n4. Frontend fetches content via API (line 274)\n5. Backend `handleAPIStepContent()` tries to read the file at path (line 1178)\n6. If file not found or error occurs, it falls through to other config types without properly signaling success/failure\n7. If all configs fail to load, returns 404 \"no content available\" (line 1198)\n8. But the drawer already shows the filename, so user sees filename but no content\n\n### **Root Causes:**\n\n1. **File Path Resolution**: The handler joins the file path with `dir` (line 1178): `filepath.Join(dir, prompt)`, but `prompt` in the config might be a relative path that doesn't resolve correctly from the project directory.\n\n2. **Silent Failures**: If `os.ReadFile()` fails (lines 1179, 1189), the code continues without logging or indicating why it failed.\n\n3. **Incomplete Error Handling**: The function returns \"no content available\" (line 1198) without distinguishing between \"file doesn't exist,\" \"permission denied,\" \"file is empty,\" etc.\n\n4. **No Fallback Display**: The frontend shows \"No content available\" but doesn't help the user understand why (missing file? wrong path? unreadable?).\n\n### **API Route and Template Summary:**\n\n- **API Endpoint**: `GET /api/projects/{name}/workflows/{workflow}/steps/{step}/content`\n- **Frontend Fetch**: Line 274 in `project_detail.html`\n- **Handler**: `handleAPIStepContent()` at `/workspace/internal/adapters/web/handler.go:1134`\n- **Drawer Component**: Lines 40-47 of `project_detail.html` (HTML structure)\n- **Drawer JavaScript Logic**: Lines 251-284 of `project_detail.html` (openDrawer function)\n\nAll relevant code is in `/workspace/internal/adapters/web/` directory, with templates in `templates/` and Go handlers in `handler.go`."}],"totalDurationMs":32613,"totalTokens":54233,"totalToolUseCount":16,"usage":{"input_tokens":0,"cache_creation_input_tokens":770,"cache_read_input_tokens":52354,"output_tokens":1109,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":770},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"}}}
